GREATER CHINA DAYBOOK: Hong Kong Tackles Inflation, Home Bubble

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-02-23T20:29:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/greater-china-daybook-hong-kong-tackles-inflation-home-bubble.html
Hong Kong Financial Secretary John
Tsang pledged to step up the fight against inflation, which he
forecast will reach 4.5 percent in the city this year. Tsang
will try to avert a housing bubble by putting more land up for
sale while helping  Hong Kong  residents through several one-off
measures such as breaks on electricity bills and payments into
pension plans.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dirk Beveridge on   dbeveridge1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:  Bruce Grant  in Hong Kong at 
 bruceg@bloomberg.net  